snippet.title: Swift: YouTube - REST JSON Integration via NSURLSession (Ep 5)
snippet.description:
In this video, we go over how to pull JSON data from the internet to build out our dynamic home feed.  First, I'll show you how to execute an NSURLSession task to complete a fetch request. Next, we iterate through all the objects in this JSON dictionary and construct all of our video objects. Finally, we update our cell images based on the image urls returned.

JSON URL used for NSURLSession request: https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/youtubeassets/home.json

Previous videos in series:
Part 1 YouTube Home Feed: https://youtu.be/3Xv1mJvwXok
Part 2 Custom Navigation Bar: https://youtu.be/APQVltARKF8
Part 3 Custom Tab Bar / Menu Bar: https://youtu.be/rRhJGnSmEKQ
Part 4 MVC Explained: https://youtu.be/Zud56x_VYvs
